Suppose $11^5\equiv n\pmod 9$, where $0\le n<9$.What is the value of $n$?
Given that $11\equiv 2\pmod 9$, we can simplify the congruence to $2^5\equiv n\pmod 9$.

To simplify $2^5\pmod 9$, we first note that $2^4 \equiv 7 \pmod{9}$ so $2^5 \equiv 2\cdot 7 \equiv 5 \pmod{9}$.

Therefore, we have $11^5 \equiv 5 \pmod 9$.
